    <h3 class="title">
      <a href="https://book.douban.com/review/5141063/" class="title-link">美国宪政简史</a>
      <div class="toggle_review right">        <a href="javascript:;" id="toggle-5141063"class="indicator unfold j" title="展开全文">        </a>
      </div>
    </h3>
    

<div class="header-more">
    <a class="author-avatar" href="https://www.douban.com/people/3814586/"><img width="48" height="48" src="https://img3.doubanio.com/icon/u3814586-2.jpg"></a>
    <a href="https://www.douban.com/people/3814586/" class="author">
      <span property="v:reviewer">Collins</span>
    </a>    <span property="v:rating" class="allstar50 main-title-rating" title="力荐"></span>
  <span property="v:dtreviewed" content="2011-10-23"
      class="main-meta">2011-10-23 22:15:18</span>
</div>

  </header>

        <div class="main-bd">
          <div id="review_5141063_short" class="review-short">
            <div class="short-content">
                  作为法学专业的学生，实际上大学里面提到美国宪政体制，更多的是三权分立，提及美国最高法院，就是马布里诉麦迪逊的经典案例。实际上，美国的宪政体制十分丰富，国会、总统、最高法院的势力此消彼长，都曾扮演过不光彩的角色。 其实，看过这本书后，我最大的感慨是，美国并非是...

                    <a class="pl" href="https://book.douban.com/review/5141063/#comments">(1回应)</a>
                  <div class="more-info pl clearfix">
                    <span class="left">5有用 / 3没用</span>
                  </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div id="review_5141063_full" class="hidden">
            <div id="review_5141063_full_content" class="full-content"></div>
          </div>
        </div>
    </div>
  </div>





